A fire broke out at an informal settlement in Zimmerman near Roysambu Primary School, Nairobi, on Monday night. The cause of the fire is yet to be established. However, a witness said it might be a case of a gas cylinder explosion. "I heard a loud sound similar to a gas cylinder explosion and on arrival at the scene, I found the place on fire," the man said. Firefighters from the Nairobi county government are at the scene. It is yet to be established whether anyone has been injured. More to follow...